properties.areaDesc: Wind River Mountains West; Upper Green River Basin Foothills
properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 15 at 1:47PM MST until February 16 at 11:00PM MST by NWS Riverton WY
properties.description:
...Winter Storm for Western Wyoming Tonight through Sunday
Evening...

.A storm system will bring significant snow across much of
western Wyoming tonight through Sunday evening.

* WHAT and WHERE...Periods of snow, moderate at times, across the
Upper Green River Basin Foothills, and the western slopes of
the Wind River Mountains. Snow accumulations will range from 6
to 12 inches in the mountains. Snowfall of 2 to 4 inches around
Pinedale with 5 to 7 inches around Bondurant. Snowfall around
South Pass will range from 2 to 3 inches along with a gusty
wind.

* WHEN...From 8 PM this evening to 11 PM Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult at times. Some
blowing snow could significantly reduce visibility including
South Pass.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Plan for adverse winter weather if
recreating this weekend.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 8 PM THIS EVENING TO 11 PM MST SUNDAY
